reviews.review_text:
Can you post the audience separately? I'm stoked you posted this recording here.

Nonetheless, if you isolate the audience 2nd set, then it will be available for download and real sharing.

thanks!

THIS IS A SHOW FOR THE AGES.  Warning: may cause powerful nightmares.

A rare and different tune.... Of the 300+ sets I had the privalage to experience, this 2nd set was musically the best I can remember. Especially the Terrapin! It has haunted me for years. Great to experience it again.......

where is the SBD of set II??? C'mon quit holdin' out already!
This Jack Straw > China/ Rider ever so slightly edges out the epic LA Forum earlier in the same month (on 12/10/89) IMO
Can't go wrong w either tho.
Everyone raves about the opener Bertha> Good Lovin' a throwback fo' sho'  it was cool. 
but set I is all about the Sugaree. 
Believe that.

1989 - The end of a dickhead ~ ;) I could never forget this Jack Straw > China > Rider. It was delicious!  I would have preferred Eyes out of Space but I'm a spoiled brat who doesn't give a flip about parenting so I just never really cared for Brent's lullaby. Kinda ironic that he sang that he'd always be there for his kids and then he bounced out on them.  A very sad tale all the way around. Nevertheless, 1989 was a very fine year!  I remember the next night at midnight, after all the balloons dropped and there was a break in the fantastic chaos, Bobby said, "My friend here tells me it's the beginning of a new dickhead, I mean decade."  hahaha! good one Bobby, keep those jokes comin',  maybe give us a smile once in awhile to let us know you're still controlling the weather,

Ru kind? Oh the irony Dude, what do you know about Brent? Did you know him, or are you just another Head speculating and/or perpetuating unfounded "Deadhead"rumors. To have the nerve to state such awful things. RU an asshole, not kind?
